1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,500
It's 12:47. Thirteen minutes to class.

2
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:12,000
And I'm seven people deep
in the canteen line.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Twenty people shouting orders.
Paper chits. Cash.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:21,000
A kitchen ten feet away
that can't hear a word.

5
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,000
A samosa is not worth
a debarred semester.

6
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:28,500
And the owner? Two bad choices.

7
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:33,500
Drown in cash and paper every rush...

8
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:38,000
or hand 15 to 30% to the delivery apps.
Commission they can't afford.

9
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:44,000
This is Tray.
Shopify for campus canteens.

10
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:48,500
A non-technical owner logs in once —
and instantly gets their canteen, online.

11
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:52,000
Admin console, kitchen view, own domain.
No code. No agency. No developers.

12
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:57,500
Students pick a canteen, see live menus
with prep times,

13
00:00:57,500 --> 00:01:01,500
and pay by U-P-I — a single-use QR.
Place the order.

14
00:01:01,500 --> 00:01:05,000
Watch it go from Placed,
to Preparing, to Ready.

15
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Pick up with a four-digit O-T-P.

16
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:10,000
In the kitchen, the ticket just appears.

17
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Incoming, preparing, ready —
then verify the O-T-P. About 300ms.

18
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:19,000
And the owner sees everything —
a live activity feed, every order,

19
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:24,000
across every canteen on campus.
One dashboard.

20
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:29,000
Zero percent commission — money settles
straight to each canteen's bank via Razorpay.

21
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Tenants are isolated in Postgres
row-level security:

22
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,500
worst case is zero rows,
never a leaked one.

23
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:40,000
Two students, one last samosa?
Only one charge goes through. By design.

24
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:45,000
The line dissolves. Students stop
waiting and start eating.

25
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:52,000
In our testing, that's about
12 minutes back — every single lunch.

26
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:56,000
Tray. Zero commission. No code.

27
00:01:56,000 --> 00:02:00,000
And the lunch line disappears.
